  "prompt": "Do Jains belong to the OBC category?",
  "response": "In India, the classification of communities into various categories such as Scheduled Castes (SC), Scheduled Tribes (ST), and Other Backward Classes (OBC) can vary by state and is subject to specific government criteria. Generally, Jains are considered a minority community and are not typically categorized as OBC in most states. However, in some regions, certain groups within the Jain community may be identified as OBC based on socio-economic conditions.\n\nIt is important to check the specific classifications in the context of a particular state or legal framework, as these classifications can differ significantly across different regions and may be updated over time. For the most accurate and detailed information, it's advisable to consult official government sources or legal documents pertaining to reservation policies in the respective state.",
